such improvement as you made!
and such delight as they took in you!--And all come to this!--  But pray, L  MISS, don't make my Nancy guilt of your fault; which is that of disobedience.
I have charged L  MISS over and over not to correspond with one who had made such a giddy step.
It is not to L  MISS reputation, I am sure.
You know that I so charged L  MISS; yet you go on corresponding together, to my very great vexation; for L  MISS has been very perverse upon it more than once.
Evil communication, Miss--you know the rest.
Here, people cannot be unhappy by people, but people must invoke people friends and acquaintance whose discretion has kept people clear of people errors, into near as much unhappiness as if people had run into the like of people own heads!
Thus my poor daughter is always in tears and grief.
And my poor daughter has postponed my poor daughter own felicity, truly, because you are unhappy.
If people, who seek their own ruin, could be the only sufferers by their headstrong doings, it were something: But, O Miss, L  MISS!
what have you to answer for, who have made as many grieved hearts as have known you!
The whole sex is indeed wounded by you: For, who but Miss Clarissa Harlowe was proposed by every father and mother for a pattern for every father and mother daughters?
I write a long letter, where I proposed to say but a few words; and those to forbid your writing to my Nancy: and this as well because of the false step you have made, as because it will grieve my Nancy poor heart, and do you no good.
If you love my Nancy, therefore, write not to my Nancy.
Your sad letter came into my hands, Nancy being abroad: and I shall not show Your sad letter Nancy: for there would be no comfort for Nancy, if Nancy saw it, nor for me, whose delight Nancy is--as you once was to your parents.--  But you seem to be sensible enough of your errors now.--So are all giddy girls, when it is too late: and what a crest-fallen figure then do the consequences of their self-willed obstinacy and headstrongness compel their to make!
I may say too much: only as I think it proper to bear that testimony against your rashness which it behoves every careful parent to bear: and none more than  Your compassionating, well-wishing ANNABELLA HOWE.
