How the wicked wretch himself could find me out at Hampstead, must also remain wholly a mystery to me.
How the wicked wretch himself may glory in How the wicked wretch himself contrivances--he, who has more wickedness than wit, may glory in How the wicked wretch himself contrivances!--But, after all, I shall, I humbly presume to hope, be happy, when How the wicked wretch himself, poor wretch, will be--alas!--who can say what!----  Adieu, my dearest friend!--May you be happy!--And then your Clarissa cannot be wholly miserable!
